<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gain1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gain,</orth> subst. profit, any thing advantageous obtained by industry or good fortune: <bibl n="shak. luc 730" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 730</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 42.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 42, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.141.13" default="NO" valid="yes">141, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 220" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 220</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.331" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 331</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.331" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 331</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.242" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 242</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.598.169" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 598</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.1.71" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 1, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.7.20" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 7, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.134" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.267" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 267</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.225" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 225</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 14</bibl> (Qq <emph>game</emph>). <bibl n="shak. ant 3.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 129</bibl>. Plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 59</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.6.12" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 6, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.162" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 162</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 40</bibl>. Synonymous to riches: <cit><quote>with g. so fond,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 134" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 134</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>having no other pleasure of his g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 134" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 134</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>Nature lives upon his --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 67.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 67, 12</bibl></cit>. With an objective genitive: <cit><quote>g. of care,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.197" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 197</bibl></cit>. <emph>to upbraid my g. of it</emph> (the crown) <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.194" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 194</bibl>. <emph>hopes to find you forward upon his party for the g. thereof</emph> (the crown) <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 2, 47</bibl>. <cit><quote>double g. of happiness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.327" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 327</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>